        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 1:17AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 117 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles west of Channing, or 26 miles north of Vega, moving southeast
at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Channing and Boys Ranch.

This includes Interstate 40 near mile marker 32.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
